    "updated_at": "2018-07-18T19:44:03Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "This would be useful. For example, around version v1.9.1 (not sure the exact version), grpc/support/thd.h was moved to grpc/support/thd_id.h. If a project wants to support GRPC versions both before and after this change, they need some way to tell whether they should `#include <grpc/support/thd.h>` or `#include <grpc/support/thd_id.h>`. (Unfortunately, adding the `#define` now won't fix this problem because it has already happened, but will help in the future with issues like this)."
